values:
There comes a time when snowflakes fall
You can see bright lights making the ground sparkle
Gentle chords soothes the ears
Little children make magic with their smiles
Colorful packages under a bushel of green
Let yourself become a child all over again
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/4541.html

Paint over the black shades
Let the brightness be present
Always keep painting with the colors of the sun
Never put the brush down
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/4273.html

When you want to let go
Look at a child
The blank canvas they behold
To put dark forlorning colors on such an innocence
Will haunt you beyond a time when your eyes close in a dark sleep
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/3935.html

You hold my heart as your prisoner
The chains are heavy
The bars are cold and unforgiving
Why won't you let my heart go?
You don't know that you hold it so tightly.
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/3757.html

You don't know
Will you ever know?
Do you even care?
I knoe you care
But does your care go beyond?
Do you have any idea?
Maybe you will never know
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/3570.html

It's like mixing dreams with the cloud you walk on
Please don't ever let me go
When you hug me I never want to let go
It's like taking the stars and mixing them with hope
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/3190.html

To play in the sand
To cry over scraped knees
Duck Duck Goose was the most intriguing game
To laughing at simple things
To swinging in the sun
When you could be the prince or the princess of the Jungle Gym Castle
To days when problems were petty
To being a child, stay one as long as you can
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/3045.html

I didn't open my eyes today
I lay awake still with my eyes closed
There wasn't a point to opening them
There was nothing in my life worth looking at
I dread the moment I would have to see my reflection
I didn't open my eyes today
I have no reason to do so
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/2574.html

A whisper of magic
Music dreams where
Castles live and the sky
Flowers pink
Once Upon a Song
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/2319.html

The twinkle of lights, a twinkle in a child's eyes
Little trinkets bring a smile
A time when there is a star for everybody
How does one hold to such wonderful things
I often want to live in this world
A place of wonder and dreams
What definition is worthy of this feeling
You are experiencing an incredible ecstasy
Up in the clouds above all is where your soul lies
The world at your finger tips
So you can fly, high like a cloud
Somewhere where a happy tear turns into a diamond
In the box on the floor
The sky was locked
But turned the key was with a twinkle in a heart
A single twinkle of faith was realized
Little bits of pink sweetness
A person can become a star
How can there be something so amazing?
I think this place is easily achieved.
The taste of wonder.
What you are is you.
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/2300.html

A little rain
Music flowing gently
Soft light
One mind
The mind reacts
And now instead of one
There are two minds
In one head
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/1831.html

Little droplets on a blank canvas
There is a young lady painted there
She sits simply, legs together
Two hands gently placed
Her skin seems flawless
Her clothes show status and taste
The little droplets are on her face
The painting was titled Blank Canvas
If this young lady was so blank
Then why are there tears rushing down her cheeks
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/1699.html

A pinch of love
A dash of sorrow
Three stars
Two hands
One ever beating heart
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/1466.html

Sometimes if you just sit and wait
Things will happen
But more often if you don't move
Nothing will ever come
Yet here I sit
Waiting for you
But you will never come
Because I continue to sit
Looking from afar
Trying to grab at something 
It's just out of reach
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/1106.html

When the leaves fall
I will be there
When the white covering melts
I will be there
When new green leaves are born
I will be there
When light pours through the clouds
I will be there
When there is so precious an object to my heart
I will always be there
When night pulls its blanket over familiar eyes
I will still be there
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/805.html

Last night I cried
It wasn't your fault
I want you to know how I feel
Some people don't understand
They don't know who they are missing
My feelings are secret
I wish I could tell you
I don't feel present with myself
I hope I can realize myself
You are loved don't worry about those who judge
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/523.html

Do I make my life difficult?
Is it a trick of the light?
I think to hard about everything
I should get paid for worrying
Because I do it like its my job
I make myself believe false truths
I am told that I can get what I want
But I feel constantly held back
Held back by what ifs and negative scenarios
Do you think I make my life difficult?
Is it a trick of my mind?
http://mskateelysia.livejournal.com/511.html
